admire:
Kathleen I cannot possibly describe all the ways that I wholeheartedly admire you. Your form is unimaginably delightful to me, your intellect challenges me and makes me laugh like only you can, your spirit overflows with compassion and love for those around you and it serves with joy. What I admire most about you is the authenticity and fervor with which you pursue the Lord with your whole heart. There is never a moment of complacency or dullness with your relationship with Him and it pours out and washes over those around you. A mentor once told me to run headlong after Jesus, giving it everything I have and every once in a while to look to my left and to my right to see if there is a woman who is keeping up with me in that same pursuit. Kathleen you are that woman and I am absolutely taken with you and blessed to be able to be in relationship with you.

I love you
favoriteMemory: I so cherish the beginning of our relationship and the foundation that we laid in that time. From Good Will Hunting to texting late at night trying to figure out your middle name and laughing loud enough to wake up my roommates, snowy evenings at Shaver and Miss Congeniality, genuine honest conversations, and nights on the futon under the stars. I can't even begin to list the memories I cherish so completely in my heart because when I do I smile as I remember yet another memory that changed my heart and my life as I fell ever more in love with you. Every single day I'm with you is another cherished memory, another sparkle of joy in my heart and shimmer of hope in my heart as I look ahead to so many more incredible memories together.
name: Eric

admire: Kathleen, I am so grateful for you! I love how bold you are in your fire, and I admire the sacrifices you've made this year to do what you are doing. I am so glad you challenged me to go to EA this past summer. I have grown so much, and it's because of your kind encouragement and the passion you have for EA. I admire that you have been able to find joy in the darkest of places, and I chat that you would continue to see glorious things all around you.
favoriteMemory:
Kathleen! Do you remember the time we went to Petco to pet puppies during Open House last spring?! I do! That was so fun! I really appreciate the way you were there for me when I was so overwhelmed that day. I just want to thank you so much for always listening to me and offering guidance. I miss group chatting with you and I just can't wait till you come back SLOme. Have a very festive birthday beautiful Kathleen! You are so loved!!!

#IWouldOnlyHaveACatForPracticalReasons
name: Molls

admire: Your Compassion. Joy. Laughter. Obedience to God's calling. Courage.
favoriteMemory: Sweet Kathleen Grigsby. There are too many moments of hysterical laughter shared between the two of us. Out of all those crazy memories, I choose Mexico, summer before freshman year of college, and drawings throughout Econ class;).
name: Emily Painter

admire: Happy Birthday Kathleen! I'm so thankful that I got to meet you this year and serve alongside you! I can't say I've ever had a friend via creeper roommate who has been praying for me, BUT nonetheless I wouldn't trade it for anything else ;) I love your heart for people, Kathleen. I know this year hasn't been easy for you, but I hope you know that you were used in so many ways and that it absolutely was not in vain. You have a big heart and everyone around you can see that passion and life you carry! I've enjoyed our sporadic conversations together and have always loved laughing with you. I hope you feel well loved and celebrated today! Love you girl!
favoriteMemory: Remember that one time we were twerking in the kitchen?! And by we, I mean you :)
name: Abigail Wong

admire: Kathleen has a kind and open heart, a great sense of humor and a wonderful grace about her that inspire me every day.  Her desire to travel to a country far from home and be a stranger in a strange land in order to help and guide others is something I will always admire and respect!
favoriteMemory: One of my favorite memories of Kathleen is the night we had pizza and orange Fanta for Thanksgiving dinner in the Piazza della Republica in Florence.  The day had been crazy and we couldn't find a restaurant that would seat the entire family so we all split up to find something to eat.  It was a cold night and all the shops were open and brightly lit as people took their evening stroll, shopping and chatting and listening to musicians play in the square.  It was a nice way to wrap up our last night in Italy.
name: Uncle Mattie

admire: Kathleen concerns herself with people.  Those relationships are what matter to her.  She can still manage tasks, but she always looks people in the face and listens to them and asks questions and deep down inside of her, she cares deeply.
favoriteMemory: When Kathleen was three years old she was riding a tricycle around the playground at Redding Cooperative Preschool.  She was laughing with her friends, the oak leaves were drifting down on the path, and her black curly hair was flying in the wind .
name: Debbie A.K.A. Momma

admire: I so admire the heart and conviction she has about her life and her deep belief in God's direction for her. Not many other people her age would, after immediately graduating from college, go on a mission so many miles away. She listens for God's voice and doesn't hesitate to heed His wishes.
favoriteMemory: Where would this family be without "for reals" unless my "potato chip incident " with Kathleen as a 4 or 5 year old had occurred. I love this memory of her and but my favorite memory of her is eating spaghetti as a little one and she has it all over her, but is smiling the sweetest smile. I have a picture of it; it's my favorite one of all my pictures of her.
name: Aunt Shannie

favoriteMemory: Kathleen!!!! It always makes me laugh when I think of all of the time we spent in spanish class. We were definitely the loudest gigglers all quarter. Ojala que no te hayas olvidado de todo tu espanol en el tiempo que has estado en China. Debes que practicar, si no se te va pasar todo el chisme cuando llegues de regreso :P
name: Edgar Nava

admire: One thing I admire about you (that goes along with what I wrote above) is the way you care for people. I can tell it is natural for you to do so. Whether it's people right in front of you like your team and Coco and Willa or people far away like your roommates and family. You care deeply and allow what other people are experiencing to impact your heart. That is true compassion.
favoriteMemory: I really appreciated your desire to get to know me and share yourself with me. Right from the beginning. You made a huge effort to come over and hang out ... even our first couple of weeks back in country. I was so grateful for that!
name: Karisa

admire: Kathleen, you have always remained strong through adversity.  Whether it was starting a new school, going to Space Camp, or travelling halfway around the world, you always had a higher calling to what you were doing.  Your Godly countenance is evident in all you do.  You embody the verse in Romans 12: 12 "Be joyful in hope, patient in affliction, faithful in prayer".  Its not just admiration I have for you, but  pride in what you have become swells my chest!
favoriteMemory: I'll never forget the couple of times we all went to a wedding and how fun it was dancing afterwards.  It reminded me of the times we would crazy dance together at the house...footloose and fancy free!
name: Apa

admire:
Dearest Kathleen,
I love the heck out of you and you have blessed my life more than you could ever know this year! If only we could have known that one summer night at your picnic debrief.... but it may have made our heads explode if we knew then. Kathleen, you have one of the most sincere and beautiful hearts that cares endlessly for the people you love. There are so many times when I wonder where it all comes from and how you do it--and that points straight to Jesus because it's only possible in Him! You have continuously shown me His love in your listening hear, your intentional and caring questions, your ability to laugh and be light hearted, in your check-in texts that make my day, and your love for Him. I leave times with you more in love with Jesus and wanting to be more like Him--and I think that is the single most important thing a human can do on this earth. I am grateful for your life of sacrifice and constant communion with Him. I love you so much, Kathleen!! Have the happiest birthday!
favoriteMemory: Late night pillow talks for days. Literally. Because we were roomies for so long in Thailand! So many gems and hilarious moments in those pillow talks :)
name: Erin Crumley

admire: You're beautiful and cool and smart and brave and wise and adventurous and impressive!! (and I can tell, even though I barely know you!)
favoriteMemory: The first time I met you! After I spent all of lunch (after church one Sunday) talking about you. You were just as awesome as I predicted!
name: Taylor McCreary

admire:

admire: I love how wise & mature you have always been, yet still able to be silly & have a good time. Maybe it's just because you're my older sister, but you have always had such sage & genuine advice for me & Caro. I always appreciated how you cared for us in that way.
favoriteMemory: My favorite memory is when you would come into my bedroom late at night when I was still working on homework (& you should already be asleep ;) ). You would sneak into my bedroom with a portable speaker & dance around me until I would finally be convinced to dance along with you ;) it always cheered me up so much in the midst of so much homework & they were evenings I'll never forget!!
name: Han

admire:
Dear one,  
I admire how you have always follow God's path for you no matter how hard it may seem.  Your journey has been long and hard this past year but I think you have learned a lot about yourself and your relationship with God.  I am so proud of your courage and your dedication.
favoriteMemory:
Kathleen,
All the Oma nights that we all spent together at my house.  You all sleeping on the living room floor.  I loved getting up in the morning and everyone would be all over the place and you would be awake and give me that wonderful smile with your hair everywhere and say "morning Oms, can I help with breakfast?" admire: I admire Kathleen's faith and love for others.  I also admire her courage in life and I admire how well she has done in school
favoriteMemory: One of my favorite memories of Kathleen is when we go to sushi.  I also love her laugh when she gets really ticked.

admire: I admire your dedication to your faith and how much you have served God recently. It is truly inspiring.
favoriteMemory: I remember having sleepovers at our grandma's (a.k.a. Oma) house with her and all of my cousins. We always had a great time!
name: Nolan Spencer

admire: Kathleen! I love how compassionate you are. You listen and let everyone know that you care about what they have to say.
favoriteMemory: While there are a thousand things I would love to talk about, my favorite memory of Kathleen is when I saw her for the first time after she got back from her first trip to East Asia. I had no idea what she had been doing there, other than sharing the Gospel, and I was so excited to hear more. That night, more than ever before, I discovered the depth of her heart. I found out how incredibly sweet-hearted, passionate, devoted, and loving she is. I had known that God had huge plans for her life, but that night, I knew for sure that she would be a world-changer.
name: Laureno :)

admire: Not only are you incredibly wise, but you know how to share that wisdom  through thoughtful questions and being bold to speak needed truth to those around you. Youre such a prayer warrior and your trust in God as you look toward the future is incredibly inspiring. Also, you can make me laugh harder and more often than anyone else in the world and I will never ever get tired of your sense of humor. Knowing you has truly been one of the biggest blessings of my time at college!
favoriteMemory: (I cant just pick one.) When we had to wake up early and so we decided that whoever got out of bed first could hit the other person with the giant foam finger When you put the tiny picture of Christopher Jame in the tiny picture frame and hung it above our door Every morning when you would sit at the table in your Shasta swimming sweatshirt and drink your coffee And every night when you would tell me goodnight little one and I would ask you if Alice and Jasper ran away because were all going to die When we learned how to moonwalk in the bathroom When I was Harold and you were the purple crayon When you spider walked through the streets of Beijing at night When we ate a candlelit dinner at our dining room table... admire: Kathleen, I love love love your willingness to go above and beyond to accommodate my weird questions and silly antics. If you can't tell-you are pretty great and I love you lots!
favoriteMemory: Wow there are so many to choose from! definitely late night study parties in the dining room! Or when you walked through the streets of Beijing with your crab walk. Also I just had a thought-I'm pretty sure you were there when us roommates had a dance party in the garage by ourselves with speakers and the bike lights on strobe effect...that was EPIC!

admire: Thanks for being always open to support me when I'm down. I appreciate your love and understanding. Your beauty is apparent to all around in form, word, and deed. The Lord's love fills you and can't help but overflow in your interactions. Telling anyone in SLO of our relation is sure to get a wide smile, in remembrance of the kindness you showed. I wish I had your ability to cultivate such deep friendships.
favoriteMemory: I remember waving at you in PCV from Drew's window. I look forward to having you in SLO again.
name: John

admire: Kathleen, you have a way of shining a light into any situation. I admire the love and happiness you project, even from so far away. It is this love, free from the fear of judgment, that has allowed us to become more like sisters than anything. I can only hope to have the same unconditional love that you do.
favoriteMemory: How can I pick just one favorite moment??! Seriously, every time we are together is my favorite. Staring with becoming otter people in Morro Bay all the way to our more recent Skype sessions. You have a unique ability to make every time we hang out the best time. I seriously cannot wait to pick up where we left off next year!
name: McKenna
